<section id=3D"introduction">
<h2><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#intr=
oduction" role=3D"doc-backlink">Introduction</a></h2>
<p>This document gives coding conventions for the Python code comprising
the standard library in the main Python distribution.  Please see the
companion informational PEP describing <a class=3D"pep reference internal" =
href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0007" title=3D"PEP 7 =E2=80=93 Style Gu=
ide for C Code">style guidelines for the C code
in the C implementation of Python</a>.</p>
<p>This document and <a class=3D"pep reference internal" href=3D"https://pe=
ps.python.org/pep-0257" title=3D"PEP 257 =E2=80=93 Docstring Conventions">P=
EP 257</a> (Docstring Conventions) were adapted from
Guido=E2=80=99s original Python Style Guide essay, with some additions from
Barry=E2=80=99s style guide <a class=3D"footnote-reference brackets" href=
=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#id6" id=3D"id1">[2]</a>.</p>
<p>This style guide evolves over time as additional conventions are
identified and past conventions are rendered obsolete by changes in
the language itself.</p>
<p>Many projects have their own coding style guidelines. In the event of an=
y
conflicts, such project-specific guides take precedence for that project.</=
p>
</section>
<section id=3D"a-foolish-consistency-is-the-hobgoblin-of-little-minds">
<h2><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#a-fo=
olish-consistency-is-the-hobgoblin-of-little-minds" role=3D"doc-backlink">A=
 Foolish Consistency is the Hobgoblin of Little Minds</a></h2>
<p>One of Guido=E2=80=99s key insights is that code is read much more often=
 than
it is written.  The guidelines provided here are intended to improve
the readability of code and make it consistent across the wide
spectrum of Python code.  As <a class=3D"pep reference internal" href=3D"ht=
tps://peps.python.org/pep-0020" title=3D"PEP 20 =E2=80=93 The Zen of Python=
">PEP 20</a> says, =E2=80=9CReadability counts=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p>A style guide is about consistency.  Consistency with this style guide
is important.  Consistency within a project is more important.
Consistency within one module or function is the most important.</p>
<p>However, know when to be inconsistent =E2=80=93 sometimes style guide
recommendations just aren=E2=80=99t applicable.  When in doubt, use your be=
st
judgment.  Look at other examples and decide what looks best.  And
don=E2=80=99t hesitate to ask!</p>
<p>In particular: do not break backwards compatibility just to comply with
this PEP!</p>
<p>Some other good reasons to ignore a particular guideline:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic simple">
<li>When applying the guideline would make the code less readable, even
for someone who is used to reading code that follows this PEP.</li>
<li>To be consistent with surrounding code that also breaks it (maybe
for historic reasons) =E2=80=93 although this is also an opportunity to
clean up someone else=E2=80=99s mess (in true XP style).</li>
<li>Because the code in question predates the introduction of the
guideline and there is no other reason to be modifying that code.</li>
<li>When the code needs to remain compatible with older versions of
Python that don=E2=80=99t support the feature recommended by the style guid=
e.</li>
</ol>
</section>
<section id=3D"code-lay-out">
<h2><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#code=
-lay-out" role=3D"doc-backlink">Code Lay-out</a></h2>
<section id=3D"indentation">
<h3><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#inde=
ntation" role=3D"doc-backlink">Indentation</a></h3>
<p>Use 4 spaces per indentation level.</p>
<p>Continuation lines should align wrapped elements either vertically
using Python=E2=80=99s implicit line joining inside parentheses, brackets a=
nd
braces, or using a <em>hanging indent</em> <a class=3D"footnote-reference b=
rackets" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#fn-hi" id=3D"id2">[1]</a=
>.  When using a hanging
indent the following should be considered; there should be no
arguments on the first line and further indentation should be used to
clearly distinguish itself as a continuation line:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre>=
<span></span><span class=3D"c1"># Correct:</span>

<span class=3D"c1"># Aligned with opening delimiter.</span>
<span class=3D"n">foo</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n"=
>long_function_name</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">var_o=
ne</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">var_two</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">,</span>
                         <span class=3D"n">var_three</span><span class=3D"p=
">,</span> <span class=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>

<span class=3D"c1"># Add 4 spaces (an extra level of indentation) to distin=
guish arguments from the rest.</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span> <span class=3D"nf">long_function_name</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">(</span>
        <span class=3D"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span cl=
ass=3D"n">var_two</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">var_th=
ree</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
        <span class=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">):</span>
    <span class=3D"nb">print</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D=
"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>

<span class=3D"c1"># Hanging indents should add a level.</span>
<span class=3D"n">foo</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n"=
>long_function_name</span><span class=3D"p">(</span>
    <span class=3D"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=
=3D"n">var_two</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
    <span class=3D"n">var_three</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span clas=
s=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre>=
<span></span><span class=3D"c1"># Wrong:</span>

<span class=3D"c1"># Arguments on first line forbidden when not using verti=
cal alignment.</span>
<span class=3D"n">foo</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n"=
>long_function_name</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"n">var_o=
ne</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">var_two</span><span c=
lass=3D"p">,</span>
    <span class=3D"n">var_three</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span clas=
s=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>

<span class=3D"c1"># Further indentation required as indentation is not dis=
tinguishable.</span>
<span class=3D"k">def</span> <span class=3D"nf">long_function_name</span><s=
pan class=3D"p">(</span>
    <span class=3D"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=
=3D"n">var_two</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">var_three=
</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
    <span class=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">):</span>
    <span class=3D"nb">print</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D=
"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p>The 4-space rule is optional for continuation lines.</p>
<p>Optional:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre>=
<span></span><span class=3D"c1"># Hanging indents *may* be indented to othe=
r than 4 spaces.</span>
<span class=3D"n">foo</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n"=
>long_function_name</span><span class=3D"p">(</span>
  <span class=3D"n">var_one</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D=
"n">var_two</span><span class=3D"p">,</span>
  <span class=3D"n">var_three</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=
=3D"n">var_four</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
<p id=3D"multiline-if-statements">When the conditional part of an <code cla=
ss=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">if</span></code>-st=
atement is long enough to require
