<section id=3D"exception-names">
<h4><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#exce=
ption-names" role=3D"doc-backlink">Exception Names</a></h4>
<p>Because exceptions should be classes, the class naming convention
applies here.  However, you should use the suffix =E2=80=9CError=E2=80=9D o=
n your
exception names (if the exception actually is an error).</p>
</section>
<section id=3D"global-variable-names">
<h4><a class=3D"toc-backref" href=3D"https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#glob=
al-variable-names" role=3D"doc-backlink">Global Variable Names</a></h4>
<p>(Let=E2=80=99s hope that these variables are meant for use inside one mo=
dule
only.)  The conventions are about the same as those for functions.</p>
<p>Modules that are designed for use via <code class=3D"docutils literal no=
translate"><span class=3D"pre">from</span> <span class=3D"pre">M</span> <sp=
an class=3D"pre">import</span> <span class=3D"pre">*</span></code> should u=
se
the <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">__all_=
