    <span class=3D"k">return</span> <span class=3D"n">math</span><span clas=
s=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">sqrt</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><spa=
n class=3D"n">x</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</li>
<li>Use <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">''=
.startswith()</span></code> and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate=
"><span class=3D"pre">''.endswith()</span></code> instead of string
slicing to check for prefixes or suffixes.<p>startswith() and endswith() ar=
e cleaner and less error prone:</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-default notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre>=
<span></span><span class=3D"c1"># Correct:</span>
<span class=3D"k">if</span> <span class=3D"n">foo</span><span class=3D"o">.=
</span><span class=3D"n">startswith</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span c=
lass=3D"s1">'bar'</span><span class=3D"p">):</span>
